    "In addition to being cost-effective, glass offers unique thermal, optical, mechanical, and chemical properties.",
    "One of its most significant advantages is its 100% recyclability, which allows it to be recycled repeatedly without any loss in quality.",
    "However, despite this potential, only about 25% of glass waste is currently recycled, with the remaining 75% being disposed of in landfills.",
    "This practice leads to significant environmental issues, such as the wastage of resources and increased landfill volumes, which can contribute to pollution [40].",
    "The production of glass depends on various resources and is essential in several industries, including the manufacturing of electrical equipment and construction materials, where it is used in products like windows, as well as in consumer electronics such as monitors, lamps, and TVs."
